"further remarkable, that tiis passage was taken from a song attributed to Apollo, who bimself; too, unluckily had been a shepherd; and he took it from another yet more ancient, composed by the first inventor of music, and at that time a shep- herd too ; and this is one of the noblest fragments of Greek antiquity. And, because I cannot sup- pose the ingenious M. Fonteneile one of their number, who pretend to censure the Greeks, with- out being able to distinguish Greek from Ephesian characters, I shall here set down the lines from which Virgil took this passage, though none of the commentators have observed it."